Source: column-encrypt
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/vibhorkum/column_encrypt

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-column-encrypt
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-column-encrypt
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Transparent column-level encryption for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
  column_encrypt adds encrypted_text and encrypted_bytea data types for
  transparent column-level encryption in PostgreSQL.
  It uses the pgcrypto extension for AES encryption, requires
  shared_preload_libraries to load its backend hook, and installs objects into
  the fixed encrypt schema.
